# dabba drives the cluster from the operator's machine, outside the VPC, so the EKS
# API endpoint must be publicly reachable for `dabba up` (kubectl/tofu) to bootstrap
# the platform. Restricting the endpoint would require running dabba from inside the
# VPC. A hardened deployment can narrow the access CIDRs on the eks-fargate module.
AVD-AWS-0040
AVD-AWS-0041

# The EKS module's cluster/node security groups allow all egress, which pods need
# to pull images and reach AWS APIs, ACME, and the control plane. Locking egress
# down to an allowlist is impractical for a general-purpose platform cluster.
AVD-AWS-0104
